ACCOUNT_TYPE_LOCAL

public static final java.lang.String ACCOUNT_TYPE_LOCAL
A special account type used for fields that are not supposed to be synchronized with a remote service. See also SynchColumns. You can use this if you want to use the content provider for storing local data.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

GLOBAL_ID_PENDING

public static final java.lang.String GLOBAL_ID_PENDING
When you add a new row to the content provider, its GLOBAL_ID can be set to GLOBAL_ID_PENDING. This means that the row is not yet synchronized with a remote service.

If the row is synch-able the GLOBAL_ID has to be replaced with a proper global ID upon a successful first sync. If the row is private, the global ID will always be pending, i.e. it should not be used. This is the case where ACCOUNT_TYPE is set to ACCOUNT_TYPE_LOCAL.

CALLER_IS_SYNCADAPTER

public static final java.lang.String CALLER_IS_SYNCADAPTER
An optional insert, update or delete URI parameter that allows the caller to specify that it is a sync adapter.

The default value is false.

If set to true, the caller must also include ACCOUNT_NAME and ACCOUNT_TYPE as query parameters.

This parameter is of interest only for synch adapter developers. See https://github.com/UbiCollab/UbiShare/issues/19.
